# aomi-transact release checklist

Two phases. Phase 2 is gated on Phase 1 task #7 (clean scanner reports captured in repo).

---

## Phase 1 — Pass all skill scanners

### #1 — Add OWASP AST03 permission manifest to SKILL.md frontmatter
Declare a permission manifest in SKILL.md frontmatter: files (read/write paths), network (allowlisted domains, not boolean), shell (which commands), tools (which MCPs/APIs). This is the foundational AST03 control — most scanners flag skills without one.
- Spec: https://owasp.org/www-project-agentic-skills-top-10/ast03
- Required before any scanner pass will be clean.

### #2 — Run Snyk agent-scan and resolve W-code findings
```
uvx snyk-agent-scan@latest --skills ./SKILL.md
```
- Resolve all W-code findings.
- Verify exact W-code mappings against https://github.com/snyk/agent-scan/blob/main/docs/issue-codes.md before fixing — search summaries gave conflicting answers about W007/W008.
- Snyk powers agentskills.io's "non-suspicious" filter, so passing this is table stakes for several distribution channels.

### #3 — Run Cisco AI Defense skill-scanner
- Repo: https://github.com/cisco-ai-defense/skill-scanner
- Hybrid YARA + LLM-judge + behavioral dataflow.
- Supports Codex/Cursor/Claude formats so it catches cross-host issues that single-target scanners miss.
- Resolve findings.

### #4 — Wire pors/skill-audit into CI as GitHub Action
- Repo: https://github.com/pors/skill-audit
- Regex/static scanner with SARIF output, designed for CI.
- Add as a GitHub Action that runs on every PR.
- SARIF output integrates with GitHub's security tab.
- Catches regressions on future edits.

### #5 — Walk through OWASP AST01–AST10 checklist manually
- Spec: https://owasp.org/www-project-agentic-skills-top-10/
- Critical controls for aomi-transact:
  - **AST01** (Malicious Skills) — prove provenance, signed releases.
  - **AST03** (Over-Privileged) — done in #1.
  - **AST10** (Cross-Platform Reuse) — verify the same bundle is safe under Codex AND Claude AND OpenClaw.
- Document each control's status in `SECURITY.md` so reviewers can audit.

### #6 — Run NMitchem/SkillScan sandboxed runtime test
- Repo: https://github.com/NMitchem/SkillScan
- Three-stage scanner: static + LLM behavioral + Docker sandbox runtime.
- Catches behavioral issues that static scanners miss.
- Optional for most skills, recommended for transaction-signing skills since runtime behavior is the actual attack surface.

### #7 — Capture clean scanner reports as audit artifacts in repo (GATE)
- After all fixes, re-run Snyk + Cisco + pors and save outputs to `.scanner-reports/` in the repo.
- Link from README.
- Lets reviewers audit the result without re-running.
- **Gating criterion for moving to Phase 2** — if any scanner is dirty, do not advance.

---

## Phase 2 — Register in all distribution channels (blocked on #7)

### #8 — Add gh skill provenance metadata to SKILL.md frontmatter
- Spec: https://github.blog/changelog/2026-04-16-manage-agent-skills-with-github-cli/
- `gh skill` writes repository / ref / tree SHA into frontmatter on install.
- Pre-populate the schema fields so the metadata structure is right.
- Without this, GitHub CLI users lose origin tracking when the skill travels.

### #9 — Verify Codex install path with agents/openai.yaml end-to-end
- Drop the bundle into a Codex skills directory.
- Confirm SKILL.md frontmatter is read for triggers.
- Confirm `agents/openai.yaml` is read for UI metadata, invocation policy, and `tools_required`.
- Test that invocation patterns ("sign tx", "check balance") fire correctly.
- Required gate before submitting to Codex-targeting registries.

### Tier 1 — real-reach channels

### #10 — Submit to anthropics/claude-plugins-official
- Repo: https://github.com/anthropics/claude-plugins-official
- Highest-trust channel. Open PR with `marketplace.json` entry.
- End-user install becomes:
  ```
  /plugin marketplace add anthropics/claude-code
  /plugin install aomi-transact
  ```
- Acceptance is curated and not guaranteed; budget review time.

### #11 — Self-host marketplace.json at repo root as fallback
- Expose `marketplace.json` at the `aomi-labs/skills` repo root.
- Lets users run:
  ```
  /plugin marketplace add aomi-labs/skills
  /plugin install aomi-transact
  ```
- Most important channel after the official one — it's the canonical install path that doesn't depend on Anthropic's curation.

### #17 — PR aomi-transact into antigravity-awesome-skills catalog
- Repo: https://github.com/sickn33/antigravity-awesome-skills
- Multi-host installer:
  ```
  npx antigravity-awesome-skills --claude
  npx antigravity-awesome-skills --codex
  npx antigravity-awesome-skills --cursor
  npx antigravity-awesome-skills --gemini
  npx antigravity-awesome-skills --antigravity
  ```
- One PR adds aomi-transact to all five host installers at once. High-leverage submission.

### Tier 2 — catalog visibility

### #12 — Submit listing to claudemarketplaces.com
- https://claudemarketplaces.com — discovery/catalog site for Claude Code plugins.
- Find the submission flow (likely a form or GitHub issue).

### #13 — Submit listing to skillsmp.com
- https://skillsmp.com — multi-host marketplace (Claude / Codex / ChatGPT).
- One of the few cross-host registries.

### #14 — Submit listing to agensi.io
- https://agensi.io — registry with install guides and curated catalog.
- Backed by Snyk Skill Inspector for the "non-suspicious" filter.
- Submission requires clean Snyk agent-scan output (handled in Phase 1).
- Most quality-gated registry.

### #15 — Submit listing to lobehub.com/skills
- https://lobehub.com/skills — large mirror/registry.
- Submit and link back to canonical GitHub repo so users get authoritative source.

### #16 — Submit to cryptoskill.org via GitHub issue template
- Crypto-specific registry, directly relevant for a tx-signing skill.
- Submit at: https://github.com/jiayaoqijia/cryptoskill/issues/new?template=skill_submission.md
- Category: `ai-crypto` (primary). Cross-list under `wallets` / `trading`.
- Single-maintainer registry — treat as visibility play, not trust signal.

### #18 — PR aomi-transact into ccpi catalog
- Repo: https://github.com/jeremylongshore/claude-code-plugins-plus-skills
- Ships its own `ccpi` package manager (npm-style).
- Open PR to add aomi-transact.

### Tier 3 — skip unless evidence demands

### #19 — Optional: publish to clawhub for OpenClaw ecosystem
- https://clawhub.ai — OpenClaw skill registry (third-party, separate ecosystem from Claude).
  ```
  clawhub login
  clawhub publish
  ```
- Low priority: small audience and adds a third-party trust hop.
- Skip unless you have evidence of OpenClaw users specifically.

### Final verification

### #20 — Verify end-to-end install on a fresh machine across 3+ channels
- On a clean machine:
  - (a) `/plugin install` via Claude Code
  - (b) `gh skill install`
  - (c) one community installer (`npx antigravity-awesome-skills` or `ccpi`)
- Confirm SKILL.md frontmatter triggers correctly on each host.
- Confirm a representative flow (e.g. "check balance") works end-to-end.
- If any channel is broken, fix before announcing.
- Blocked on #7, #10, #11, #17.
